Create an account on Xilinx website.
Install the Xilinx ISE WebPACK (Linux or Windows).
Extract the tar and run: sudo ./xsetup
Select the ISE WebPACK.
Setup environment variables with: . /opt/Xilinx/14.7/ISE_DS/settings64.sh
Run: ise
Go to www.xilinx.com\getlicense and generate a free ISE WebPACK license.
Download the xilinx.lic file and load it using the license manager.

Setup papilio loader:
sudo apt-get install libftdi1:i386 # Need the 32bit libftdi1
Program using: papilio-loader-gui # Run the gui loader

Follow the tutorial at: http://papilio.cc/index.php?n=Papilio.GettingStarted
Hook up scope to even pins and see square wave.
Use screen to see serial output over USB: screen /dev/serial/by-id/usb-FTDI_Dual_RS232-if01-port0

